# Quick Setup Instructions:

## 1. Create Project Directory
mkdir company-news-backend
cd company-news-backend

## 2. Initialize Project
npm init -y

## 3. Install Dependencies
npm install express cors axios dotenv
npm install --save-dev nodemon

## 4. Create server.js
# Copy the Node.js backend code from the artifact above

## 5. Update package.json scripts
# Add the scripts section shown above

## 6. Run the Server
npm run dev
# OR
npm start

## 7. Test the API
# Open browser and visit:
# http://localhost:3001
# http://localhost:3001/api/company-news/Apple
# http://localhost:3001/api/search-symbol/Tesla

## 8. Start Your Frontend
# Your React app should now connect to http://localhost:3001

## API Endpoints Available:
GET /                                    # Health check
GET /api/company-news/:companyName       # Get news for company
GET /api/search-symbol/:companyName      # Find stock symbol
GET /api/company-info/:symbol            # Get financial data

## Rate Limits:
- NewsAPI: 1,000 requests/month (free tier)
- Alpha Vantage: 5 requests/minute, 500/day (free tier)

## Troubleshooting:
- If port 3001 is busy, change PORT in .env file
- Check console for detailed error messages
- Ensure your frontend calls http://localhost:3001 (not https)
